      },
      "date": "2020-11-12 01:11:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nSo in RHEL7 they added a new \"struct file_operations_extend\" which contains the original struct file_operation; as kabi_ops field; and the hooks for function pointers like copy_file_range. You have to register this extended fops with register_fo_extend() which influenced my new function naming. If you look for cifs_file_ops in cifsfs.c in the RHEL7 kernel source you will see this craziness.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
